                type="document" xml:id="d182">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>During the morning of Saturday, October 23, <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                        >Dulles</persName>, accompanied by General <persName
                        corresp="#p_GRUENTHERAM1">Gruenther</persName>, spoke with <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MACMILLANH1"
                        >Macmillan</persName> concerning the stationing of their troops in Trieste,
                    and the British gave the impression that these troops would not be sent to
                    Austria but would be brought home. <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                        >Dulles</persName> then spoke with <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1"
                        >Eden</persName> about the British pledge to help finance <gloss
                        target="#t_UNRRA1">UNRRA</gloss>. Summaries of the discussion of these two
                    subjects were transmitted to the Department of State in telegrams <gloss
                        target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 14 and 15 from Paris, October 23; telegram
                        <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 14 is printed in the compilation on
                    Austria in <ref target="frus1952-54v07p1">volume VII</ref>. Telegram <gloss
                        target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 15, not printed, is in Department of State
                    file 357.AD/10–2354.</p>
            </div>
